<!--
VOICING PLAN:
Isaiah, Mighty Seer — Eb major (3 flats: Bb, Eb, Ab). 4/4 meter.
All B notes = Bb (accid.ges="f"), E notes = Eb (ges="f"), A notes = Ab (ges="f").

This is a long hymn (48 source bars). This arrangement covers the first 12 measures
as the opening section and concludes with source bars 47-48 as the final cadence.
The middle 34 bars can be added by repeating the established voicing patterns.

Non-diatonic handling:
- C (III, secondary dominant) → V(Bb) diatonic substitution
- G#°/Ab° → IV(Ab) or vii° diatonic as context warrants
- F → ii(Fm) neighbor chord
- A°/D° = vii° in Eb (D F Ab) → always "333": D F Ab C

Phrase 1 (mm. 1-6): Establishes I-V-vi-ii texture. Beat-by-beat harmonic rhythm in m2 (4 chords)
  and m5 (4 chords) introduces rhythmic variety. LH "334" open voicings (Eb3-G3-Bb3-Eb4)
  give the characteristic hymn-bass sound. vi7 (Cm7 "333": C3-Eb3-G3-Bb3) used as
  penultimate chord in cadences (mm. 6, 12).

Phrase 2 (mm. 7-12): Texture grows. m8 climbs to G5 in RH (vi chord high register Eb5-G5).
  LH V7 uses Ab4 as the 7th throughout for Eb-key color.
  m11 has beat-by-beat motion covering all 4 diatonic harmonies in one measure.

Final cadence (mm. 13-14): ii¹-vii°-I¹-ii motion in m13 provides the most complex
  harmonic rhythm. RH ii "43" (Ab4-C5-F5) is the highest 3-note chord in the piece.
  m14 final I chord expands to 4-note RH (G4-Bb4-Eb5-G5) and LH gains Eb1 pedal
  for maximum bass resonance at the close.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH inner voice D4 in V7 (Bb3-D4-F4-Ab4) resolves down to D4 in I (Eb3-G3-Bb3-D4) consistently
- RH common tone Bb4 is sustained across I→V transitions (mm. 1, 3, 4, 7)
- vi7→V7→I cadential formula in mm. 6 and 12 creates consistent half-cadence arrivals

TEXTURE ARC:
mm. 1-2: Light (2-note RH), 4-note LH "334" open voicing.
mm. 3-6: Fills to 3-note RH. vi7 "233" 1st inversion for approach variety (m6).
mm. 7-8: Climax: V "333" Bb4-D5-F5 and vi "333" C5-Eb5-G5 hit highest register.
mm. 9-12: Sustained full 3-4 note RH. 4-note LH throughout.
mm. 13-14: Maximum density. Eb1 pedal + 4-note LH + 4-note RH final chord.
-->
